The paper deals with the concept of rate-distortion theory, which is a fundamental concept in information theory and data compression. The paper also discusses the Kolmogorov complexity, which is a concept related to algorithmic information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with the analysis of possible shapes of rate-distortion graphs, which is related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also discusses the "essence" or "meaning" of compressed data, which is related to machine learning and natural language processing, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses lossy compression, which is related to multimedia and computer vision, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) likely categories as well.
